#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.15"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.15:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.15:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. Rule"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.15:0.3"
msgid "15. Mānasasutta"
msgstr "15. A Mental Snare"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.15:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn4.15:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn4.15:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.249"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.15:2.1"
msgid "“Antalikkhacaro pāso,"
msgstr "“There’s a mental snare"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.15:2.2"
msgid "yvāyaṃ carati mānaso;"
msgstr "wandering the sky."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.15:2.3"
msgid "Tena taṃ bādhayissāmi,"
msgstr "I’ll bind you with it—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.15:2.4"
msgid "na me samaṇa mokkhasī”ti."
msgstr "you won’t escape me, ascetic!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.15:3.1"
msgid "“Rūpā saddā rasā gandhā,"
msgstr "“Sights, sounds, tastes, smells,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.15:3.2"
msgid "Phoṭṭhabbā ca manoramā;"
msgstr "and touches so delightful:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.15:3.3"
msgid "Ettha me vigato chando,"
msgstr "desire for these is gone from me."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.15:3.4"
msgid "Nihato tvamasi antakā”ti."
msgstr "You’re beaten, terminator!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.15:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ bhagavā, jānāti maṃ sugato”ti dukkhī "
"dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!”"
" miserable and sad, vanished right there."
